Lassa fever, imported - Germany ex W.Africa (02) 20000113145922
[1
Date: Thu, 13 Jan 2000 22:59:37 +0100
From: "Saraiva da Cunha" <saraivainf@mail.telepac.pt>

The patient came from Africa by Portuguese airways (TAP Air Portugal) flight
TP3149 from Abidjan, 6 Jan 2000, in transit through Lisbon airport.
Portuguese Health Authorities are calling all the 74 passengers of this
flight to be alert to symptoms of flu-like illness and immediately seek
medical assistance. But the influenza A crisis in Europe is a much more
probable cause of any symptoms in these travellers.
This event should be an alert to Portuguese Health Authorities to put in
place a strategic plan to deal with cases of probable hemorrhagic fevers.
Portuguese Hospitals are not prepared to safely treat these patients.
--
